=== Noun ===
'''jibber''' ([[jibbers]])

#a horse that [[jibs|Jib]], i.e. refuses, stops short.
#someone who backs out of plans at the last minute, often with a poor excuse, disappointing others.
# ('''jibber''') Someone who keeps going to the post office so as to avoid going top the pub with his mates.
# By extension, this term applies to all those who never turn up when invited (see usage note).

=== Etymology ===
This word was created after Mr P.B, and his passion for the St Genis post-office.

